  <rte>
    <name>Staveley Tarns circular</name>
	<desc>This Lake District walk explores part of a lesser known area of the National Park away from the tourist traps of nearby Windermere, Bowness and Ambleside. The walk includes three tarns but no tops.</desc>
	<author>Copyright Walking Britain</author>
	<url>www.walkingbritain.co.uk/walk-1049-description</url>
